articles.description: Freshman Ledarrius Brewer scored 34 points with seven 3-pointers -- both career-highs -- and Southeast Missouri State jumped ahead early to defeat Eastern Illinois 80-73 Thursday night.
articles.headline: Brewer scores 34, paces Southeast Missouri St. to 80-73 win

articles.description: C.J. Burks scored a career-high 36 points with six 3-pointers, Jon Elmore added 28 points, six assists and seven rebounds and Marshall defeated Rice 93-80 Thursday night.
articles.headline: Burks scores 36, Marshall overtakes Rice 93-80

articles.description: Delano Spencer sank a career-best seven 3-pointers on his way to a career-high 32 points and Tennessee State held off Morehead State 83-74 on Thursday night for its seventh straight victory.
articles.headline: Spencer sparks Tennessee State past Morehead State 83-74

articles.description: Bryce Washington scored 19 points while grabbing 10 rebounds to help Louisiana to a 73-63 win over Texas State on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Washington leads Louisiana to 73-63 win over Texas State

articles.description: Geno Crandall scored North Dakota's only two baskets in the final eight minutes, but his second one with 17 seconds left was enough to give the Fighting Hawks a 61-57 victory over Southern Utah in a Big Sky Conference clash Thursday night.
articles.headline: Crandall lifts North Dakota past Southern Utah, 61-57

articles.description: Chimezie Metu's layup with 0.8 seconds remaining lifted Southern California to a 72-70 victory over Oregon on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Metu's layup with 0.8 left wins it for USC, 72-70

images.caption: USC's Jordan McLaughlin finds Chimezie Metu inside to give the Trojans the winning bucket over the Ducks.
images.name: Trojans win on alley-oop
